📌 Overview

This lab demonstrates deploying a containerized web application using:

Linux Virtual Machine

Docker

Azure Container Registry (ACR)

Azure Container Instances (ACI)

🧱 Architecture
Local VM (Docker)
     ↓
Container Image
     ↓
Azure Container Registry (ACR)
     ↓
Azure Container Instances (ACI)
     ↓
Public Web App
⚙️ Technologies Used

Microsoft Azure

Docker

Azure Container Registry

Azure Container Instances

Linux (Ubuntu)

🧪 Steps Performed
1. Created Linux VM

Ubuntu Server

Opened ports 22 and 80

2. Installed Docker
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
3. Created Web App
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello from Azure Container Lab!"

app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=80)
4. Created Dockerfile
FROM python:3.9
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN pip install flask
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
5. Built & Ran Container
docker build -t mywebapp .
docker run -d -p 80:80 mywebapp
6. Pushed Image to ACR
docker tag mywebapp <registry>.azurecr.io/mywebapp
docker push <registry>.azurecr.io/mywebapp
7. Deployed with ACI

Used Azure Portal

Exposed port 80

Assigned DNS name

🌐 Result

Application successfully deployed and accessible via public URL.
